    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - STRIKER PIN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STRIKER PIN</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601847">Figure 47</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601847" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601847" filename="../figg16/G1601847.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Striker Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LATCH PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN 34 TO 50 FT-LBS. (46 TO 68 NM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TORX HEAD TOOL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPACER SHIM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Door striker pin (Item 2) mounted on door latch pillar (Item 1) provides positive engagement with door
                latch assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601848">Item 1, Figure 48</hotlnk>). Striker pin removal and installation requires a
                torx head tool (Item 3). Enlarged mounting hole and tapped block in door latch pillar permits
                adjustment.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601848" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601848" filename="../figg16/G1601848.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Door Latch Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. DOOR LATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a torx head tool (Item 3) to remove door striker pin (Item 2) from latch pillar
                    (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If spacer shims (Item 4) are used between latch pillar (Item 1) and door striker pin
                    (Item 2), save and reuse during installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin (Item 2) was removed, position spacer shims (Item 4), if so
                    equipped, in place on the latch pillar (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door striker pin (Item 2) by threading it into the latch pillar (Item 1) with a
                    torx head tool (Item 3). Tighten to 34 to 50 ft-lbs. (46 to 68 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin adjustment is required, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_50.xml" xrefid="hl1601804">ADJUSTMENTS, STRIKER PIN
                        <xref refid="hl1601804"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
